MINNA – Three persons have lost their lives while 33 others suffered various degrees of injuries in an accident along Gwachipe bridge along the, Suleja-Lam­bata bridge on Wednesday in Niger State. The accident which oc­curred at about noon due to over speeding is said to have been caused by a trailer con­veying goods and persons was heading to Lagos from Kano when the driver lost control as it made its way to cross the bridge. The trailer, our correspon­dent gathered was also over­loaded, carrying both human and goods apparently meant for the Christmas supply but unfortunately it lost control while trying to cross the bridge as it crashed. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Meanwhile, the Sule­ja-Lambata outpost of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) who was on rescue mission to the scene of the accident and evacuated the victims to the nearby hospi­tal confirmed the accident. Also, the Niger State Sector Commander, Corps Commander Joel Dagwa attributed the crash to reck­lessness on the part of the driver. “We had a lone crash which involved a commer­cial trailer without any plate number from Kano heading to Lagos.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION